<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Coucou</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Loads of useless tests</h1>
  <p>
    <{
      "co<i>ucou"
    }>
  </p>
  <p>
    <{<[<i>yoyoyo</i>]>}>

    <{"coucou" ++ "coucou"}>
  </p>
  <!--
    <{"-->"}> hmm...
  -->
  <{ <[<strong>coucou</strong> <{"<strong>actuallyastring</strong>"}>]> }>
  <h2>Couple</h2>
  <p>
    <{ let couple = (1, 2) }>

    couple: <{ couple }><br/>
    first: <{ fst couple }><br/>
    second: <{ snd couple }>
  </p>
  <h2>Form</h2>
  <p>
    <form method="GET" action="randomtarget.tml">
      <input id="1" type="text" name="nom"></input>
      <input id="2" type="submit" value="Envoyer"></input>
    </form>
  </p>
  <h2>Tests on strings</h2>
  <p>
    <{ "\tcoucou" }>

    <{ "cou'c\'ou\0\ncoucou2\rcoucou3enfait\"\tautre" }>
  </p>
  <h2>Variable names</h2>
  <p>
    <{
      let _x = 5 in _x
    }>
    <{
      let _x = 5 in _x
    }>
  </p>
  <h2>Characters/Strings</h2>
  <p>
    <{
      let s = "coucou : #sym.alpha"
      let t = f"cou%{fun x -> x}%cou"
    }>
    s: <{s}><br/>
    9th char of s: <{String.get s 9}><br/>
    t: <{t}><br/>
    <{
      let i = 3 in
      f"%{i}%-th char of t: %{String.get t i}%"
    }>
  </p>
  <h2>Codex</h2>
  <p>
    <{ let myArrow = <[ #sym.arrow.wave ]> }>
    An arrow from tresml codeblock! : <{ f"\#sym.arrow = %{let x = 5 in x}%" ++ "#sym.arrow.r.squiggly" }><br/>
    Another directly in the toplevel HTML: #sym.emptyset.arrow.r <br/>
    Another other from HTML block within tresml: <{ myArrow }> 
  </p>
  En Typst, je peux écrire <code>\#sym.arrow.r</code> pour ...
  #emoji.face
  #emoji.warning
  <script type="text/javascript">
    <{
      let truc2 = "cou\");ou" in
      <[
        alert("<{truc2}>");
        </script>
        <{
          truc2
        }>
      ]>
    }>
</body>
</html>